==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spongiolite
<hw>Spon"gi*o*lite</hw> <pr>(-⟦osl⟧*l⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>spoggia`</grk> sponge + <ets>-lite</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>One of the microscopic siliceous spicules
which occur abundantly in the texture of sponges, and are sometimes
found fossil, as in flints.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spongiopilin</ent>⟦br⟧
